result.execSummary:
The defendant McKenzie A Hansen was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[MK] case called at 2:54pm. 
Attorney John Vernon Rhiel in court.  DA Susan Happ appears for the State of Wisconsin.
This case is scheduled for Initial Apperance today, however Defendant McKenzie Hansen does not appear. 
The Court finds probable cause to exist in the Criminal Complaint.
The Court appoints Attorney Rhiel as counsel in this case; any attorney fee reimbursement plan is applied to this case also. 
Attorney Rhiel indicates that he has been trying to reach Ms. Hansen by telephone today, to remind her that she needs to appear. 
Attorney Rhiel notes that Ms. Hansen has a hearing scheduled for later afternoon on a separate case.
DA Happ indicates that she has no objection to adjourning briefly to await the 3:30 hearing time in that separate case.
The Court orders issuance of a probable cause warrant-- to include a provision that Ms. Hansen may post $500 cash bail in lieu of arrest as long as the bond form gives a new court date for Ms. Hansen to appear. 
recess 2:59pm.
